The '''Jedi Training Center'''<ref name="DFRS">''[[Dark Force Rising Sourcebook]]''</ref> on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Kamparas]] was an [[Jedi academy|academy]] used by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] during the age of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="TJP" /> Among the members of the Order, the Kamparas facility was considered among one of the most important [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] establishments along with the [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] and the [[Great Jedi Library/Legends|Great Jedi Library]] of [[Ossus/Legends|Ossus]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

==History==
Established sometime before the [[New Sith Wars]] by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], the Kamaparas facility was known for its specialization in data collection and storage. Home to many [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Lore Keeper]]s, this academy often hosted [[Clan (Jedi)/Legends|clans]] of [[Jedi Initiate/Legends|Jedi Initiates]] from the [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] Temple for specialized training.<ref name="BC">{{DB|organization|bearclan|Bear Clan}}</ref>

During the final [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the Republic the academy hosted some of the brightest minds of the era. [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Yaddle/Legends|Yaddle]] made this facility her residence when she wasn't on Coruscant, overseeing study and tutelage within the academy.<ref name="Yaddle">{{DB|character|yaddle|Yaddle}}</ref> Both [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]] [[Jorus C'baoth]] and [[Lexia Ginorra]] studied here, going on to do great deeds on behalf of the Order.<ref name="CatCW">''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]''</ref><ref name="DFRS" /> During the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]] leading up to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the facility came into the spotlight when it received a shipment of tax-payer purchased [[Delta-7 Aethersprite-class light interceptor/Legends|Delta-7 ''Aethersprite''-class light interceptors]] and later during the [["Baby Ludi" custody case]].<ref name="Hnn-New Jedi Starfighter Unveiled">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|47|jediwatch/13314_1.html|New Jedi Starfighter Unveiled}}</ref> The Order moved the clan of which [[Aris-Del Wari]], or "Baby Ludi", was a part of during the highly publicized debate surrounding the Order's acquisition of the child without the mother's consent.<ref name="Hnn-Baby Ludi Moved to Kamparas">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|52|jediwatch/13418_1.html|Baby Ludi Moved to Kamparas}}</ref>

According to [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious's]] notes in his stolen copy of ''[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force]]'', the Kamparas facility was one of many that he was able to locate and secure during the [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|Great Jedi Purge]] after learning of the academy's location in the pages of the Jedi text. The [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] later agreed to terms with the [[Bounty Hunters' Guild/Legends|Bounty Hunters' Guild]], allowing members of the guild to use the facilities as a training facility.<ref name="BHC" />

